place.name: ST DOMINICK
place.gazetteerText: DOMINICK (St.), a parish in Liskeard district, Cornwall; on the river Tamar, at the boundary with Devon, 3 miles SE of Callington, and 5 N by W of Saltash r. station. Post town, Callington, Cornwall. Acres, 3, 226; of which 100 are water. Real property, £4, 056. Pop., 862. Houses, 185. Halton here was the birth-place of Rous, the friend of Cromwell. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Exeter. Value, £318.* Patron, the Rev. F. L. Bazeley. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
